<br>
I did, however, consider it cosmic justice for what your group was doing.  You were training everyone else, and then you got trained; however,I did not cause that train.<br>
<br>
Nor did I say &quot;ha ha now you know how it feels&quot;.  I believe the words were &quot;what goes around comes around threefold&quot;, a Wiccan proverb.<br>
<br>
Yes, the Shield of Brambles was an attempt at making amends.<br>
<br>
Fritz, I didn't bring up this issue.  You have.  I didn't come here and complain about it.  You have.  I was perfectly willing to let that issue go that night.  I haven't come here to complain about the group that trained DVinn three times in an hour (killing me twice that night), either.  (He killed a lot of other people, too, and that group held your attitude: &quot;don't play on the train tracks&quot;.  It didn't fly with anyone who DVinn killed in that hour.  A lot of people were angry at this irresponsible group who kept saying &quot;we almost had him!&quot; as they sat there with sliver of health, and DVinn raged inside with all but a sliver of health.  They weren't anywhere close to having had him.)<br>
